<body>
    <h1>HTML Hyperlinks Demonstration</h1>
    <p>Hyperlinks in HTML are created using the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tag with the <code>href</code> attribute to specify the link destination. The <code>target</code> attribute determines how the link is opened.</p>

    <h2>Basic Hyperlink</h2>
    <p>Visit the <a href="https://www.google.com" target="_self">Google</a> website. (Opens in the same tab.)</p>

    <h2>Open Link in a New Tab</h2>
    <p>Visit the <a href="https://www.wikipedia.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Wikipedia</a> website. (Opens in a new tab.)</p>

    <h2>Open Link in Parent Frame</h2>
    <p>If this page is inside a frame, visit <a href="https://www.example.com" target="_parent">Example</a> in the parent frame.</p>

    <h2>Open Link in Full Window</h2>
    <p>Visit <a href="https://www.bbc.com" target="_top">BBC News</a> to load in the full browser window.</p>

    <h2 id="bottom">Bottom of the Page</h2>
    <p>You have reached the bottom of the page!</p>
</body>
